<html>
    <head>
        <style>
            /* Add your styles here for better button appearance */
            .button-container {
                margin-top: 20px;
            }
            .button-container button {
                padding: 10px 20px;
                margin-right: 10px;
                border: none;
                border-radius: 5px;
                cursor: pointer;
                font-weight: bold;
            }
            .accept-button {
                background-color: #4CAF50; /* Green */
                color: white;
            }
            .reject-button {
                background-color: #f44336; /* Red */
                color: white;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Hi Ravi,</p>
        <p>The person: **{{name}}** has created an account and is requesting a password. You can choose to accept or reject the user's request.</p>
        <div class="button-container">
            <form action="{{accept}}" method="POST" style="display: inline-block;">
                <button type="submit" class="accept-button">Accept</button>
            </form>
            <form action="{{reject}}" method="POST" style="display: inline-block;">
                <button type="submit" class="reject-button">Reject</button>
            </form>
        </div>
        <p>
            You can also directly use these links if the buttons don't work:
            <br>
            Accept: <a href="{{accept}}">{{accept}}</a>
            <br>
            Reject: <a href="{{reject}}">{{reject}}</a>
        </p>
    </body>
</html>